{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_20","type":"reasoning","text":"**Considering performance issues**\n\nI think there might be a performance issue here. I need to inspect the PartnerShell text further, as it seems to provide the currentUser and partner in the context of the child. Using `usePartnerAccess` could help reuse data, since `ProfileContent` can call it to get the current user and partner, along with their loading states. \n\nHowever, since the Profile page wants to allow authenticated user profile editing, it may need the email and full name, which `currentUser` already provides. The partner data is also loaded there, so it risks duplicating `auth.me` and `Partner.get`, leading to redundant network calls and slower loads. I should check the `BUGS.md` for any mentions of duplicate fetches or `usePartnerAccess`."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"reasoning","text":"**Identifying accessibility issues**\n\nI've noticed some potential issues: first, the `getRoleLabel` null guard is missing, which is already active. Then there are decorative icons lacking the `aria-hidden` attribute, and the input min-height is missing, with the save button not having a fixed footer. I need to inspect the actual code for other new accessibility problems. \n\nThere's the readonly email input that lacks `aria-readonly`, but since the readOnly attribute is sufficient, that's not necessary. Also, the save button doesn't provide a description when the name field is empty, which could be seen as a lack of error handling or usability."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_22","type":"reasoning","text":"**Considering potential issues**\n\nI'm thinking about avoiding duplicates in my code. There's a potential problem where `loadUser` sets `isUserLoading` to false before the partner fetch is completed. If the partner fetch is slow and the user navigates back quickly, it could lead to issues. \n\nAlso, when `base44.auth.me()` returns undefined or null, it could crash when trying to set `userData.full_name`. I need to handle null values properly to avoid errors in the subsequent code."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"reasoning","text":"**Investigating PartnerShell structure**\n\nWhen the save is successful but before the timeout, I notice that the button is disabled due to saveStatus. If the user changes their full name quickly, they might not be able to save until the system is idle. This could be an existing issue, although it's not listed explicitly as new. It seems we've already fixed bug PF-009, so I want to avoid complicating things.\n\nNow, IΓÇÖm wondering about the structure of PartnerShell. It uses min-h-screen, but could this affect the page height or cause overflow since it likely already manages layout and scrolling? IΓÇÖll need to inspect the structure of PartnerShell further."}}
