{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"reasoning","text":"**Evaluating accessibility concerns**\n\nIΓÇÖm noticing that when a screen reader changes routes, it might not announce the page title as it did before with traditional SPA methods. The error content shows up, but it may not be automatically announced. The loading state is labeled as `role=status`, but when it disappears, the new error might not be communicated effectively. Adding `role=\"alert\"` or focusing on the heading could enhance accessibility. However, I'm wondering how impactful that might be compared to the overall min-height of the screen. We only really need a few findings, perhaps 1-3. It's vital to ensure all success and error messages are accessible too."}}
